| Issue | Solution | Security Benefit |
|-------|----------|-----------------|
| No security headers | `helmet.js` middleware | Prevents common web vulnerabilities (XSS, clickjacking, etc.) |
| No rate limiting | `express-rate-limit` | Prevents DoS attacks |
| No input validation | Query parameter validation with bounds checking | Prevents injection attacks and resource exhaustion |
| No error handling | Try-catch blocks and error middleware | Prevents information leakage |
| No CORS policy | Explicit CORS headers | Controls which origins can access the API |
| No body size limits | `express.json()` with limit | Prevents large payload attacks |
| Missing logging | Morgan + structured logging | Enables security auditing and incident response |
| Exposed errors | Environment-aware error responses | Prevents sensitive information disclosure |

